title.narrative: 4.2 STRENGTHENED CAPACITY TO DELIVER WASH SERVICES

description.narrative: 4.2 National capacity to deliver sustainable and safely managed water and sanitation services is strengthened,which contributes to Sanitation, Sanitation (Covid), Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, more Palestinian children and families, especially the most vulnerable, have access to and use affordable, sustainable and safely managed water and sanitation services, and adopt improved hygiene practices.

title.narrative: 4.2 National capacity to deliver sustainable and safely managed water and sanitation services is strengthened

description.narrative: With UNICEF support, national authorities such PWA, MoE, MoPH and CMWU have improved their capacity with better services for the provision of safe water and sanitation for the most vulnerable communities, ECDs and Health Care Facilities. In 2019, 382,417 people benefited from improved access to safe water; 17,422 from improved access to sanitation services; 162,000 people with increased access to WASH services in health centers and 57,438 people were engaged in hygiene awareness sessions and hygiene behavioural practices. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2020
